WEBVTT

00:18.888 --> 00:21.456
-[ school bell rings ]
-CLARE:
Ethel, stay behind please.

00:21.586 --> 00:24.415
-How are you?
-Like a Little
fucking Orphan Annie.

00:24.546 --> 00:27.331
Your attitude's
gonna drive people away.

00:27.462 --> 00:29.942
-What are you thinking about?
-How much I love you

00:30.073 --> 00:31.901
considering
how little I know you.

00:32.032 --> 00:33.990
Management gave you this life
in our world.

00:34.121 --> 00:36.036
Bring us Emily Burton.

00:36.166 --> 00:37.689
Every room in my embassy

00:37.820 --> 00:39.430
has been filled
with stranded crossers.

00:39.561 --> 00:42.303
When can I tell my people
we are going home?

00:42.433 --> 00:44.087
MARKOVA: That's not up to me,
Ambassador.

00:44.218 --> 00:46.263
It was your side
who closed the doors.

00:46.394 --> 00:47.656
PRIME: You want to find
a way out of this?

00:47.786 --> 00:49.223
You're gonna have
to handle it yourself.

00:49.353 --> 00:50.441
I left a gun in the men's room.

00:50.572 --> 00:52.661
I think it's time
you bring this to an end.

00:53.662 --> 00:54.967
"Hi, Clare.

00:55.098 --> 00:56.534
"The main server crashed,

00:56.665 --> 00:58.362
and we have to stay
at the office."

00:58.493 --> 01:00.886
Clare, I love you.

01:01.017 --> 01:03.846
-I wanted so badly
to see the dream become real.
-Wait!

01:03.976 --> 01:05.891
-No, fuck!
-TEMPLE: Peter...

01:06.022 --> 01:08.372
-it's over.
-She was Shadow.

01:08.503 --> 01:10.592
-Where are you now?
-EMILY PRIME:
I think this is Echo.

01:10.722 --> 01:12.942
-There's shooting.
-No!

01:13.073 --> 01:14.596
-SHAW: Em, slow down.
-EMILY PRIME:
Something's happened.

01:14.726 --> 01:16.119
-No time.
-SHAW: Em. Em!

01:18.774 --> 01:19.557
YANEK:
You will never

01:19.688 --> 01:21.559
get them to close
the doors forever.

01:21.690 --> 01:23.518
The blood of millions
is on your hands,

01:23.648 --> 01:26.173
and I won't stand by any longer.

01:26.303 --> 01:28.610
I want to meet all of you.
Together.

01:39.838 --> 01:42.276
MIRA:
My terms are simple:

01:42.406 --> 01:46.193
shut down the Crossing forever.

01:46.323 --> 01:50.066
I want you to invite
our neighbors for a meeting.

01:50.197 --> 01:53.025
Tomorrow I will surrender
myself and my father

01:53.156 --> 01:55.767
to your custody.

01:55.898 --> 01:58.205
I want to meet all of you.

01:58.335 --> 02:00.598
Together.

02:00.729 --> 02:02.513
The choice is yours.

02:08.302 --> 02:12.697
[ speaking German ]

02:44.468 --> 02:47.167
[ door opens, closes ]

02:59.440 --> 03:02.269
For the Fourth Floor
on your side.

03:02.399 --> 03:04.184
You're going home, Ambassador.

03:28.382 --> 03:30.210
[ alarm blaring ]

03:57.367 --> 03:59.369
♪

03:59.500 --> 04:00.457
You okay?

04:03.895 --> 04:05.767
They want to meet.

04:10.206 --> 04:12.252
♪

04:39.540 --> 04:42.456
♪

05:09.047 --> 05:10.962
♪

05:32.549 --> 05:34.421
[ man panting ]

05:36.553 --> 05:39.034
[ door opens ]

05:41.471 --> 05:43.343
[ men grunting ]

05:50.393 --> 05:54.919
There are rules in place
for a reason, Wesley.

05:57.139 --> 05:59.489
Thought I taught you that.

05:59.620 --> 06:01.273
I know I taught you that.

06:03.363 --> 06:05.495
[ sighs ]

06:05.626 --> 06:08.368
It's the same news,
whether you look now or later.

06:25.167 --> 06:28.170
[ exhales ]

06:46.275 --> 06:48.233
[ crying ]

06:48.364 --> 06:51.759
She had nothing to do with this.

06:51.889 --> 06:53.761
She didn't.

06:53.891 --> 06:55.545
You're right.

06:57.678 --> 07:01.246
But you couldn't keep
a simple goddamn secret

07:01.377 --> 07:04.249
from your simple goddamn wife.

07:04.380 --> 07:06.948
We just came to talk to her,

07:07.078 --> 07:11.343
but she got spooked,
ran, took a fall.

07:11.474 --> 07:14.085
It shouldn't have happened
this way.

07:14.216 --> 07:18.046
My condolences, Wesley Pierce.
You're officially dead.

07:18.176 --> 07:20.396
This is your new life.

07:20.527 --> 07:24.052
Your name is Ian Shaw,
resident of the other side.

07:24.182 --> 07:26.010
Agent in Housekeeping.

07:26.141 --> 07:27.838
Sorry about the name.

07:27.969 --> 07:29.666
They would've just set you up
in your other's life,

07:29.797 --> 07:31.799
but, uh, he didn't make it out
of the flu.

07:34.279 --> 07:37.805
SHAW:
I don't understand.

07:37.935 --> 07:41.025
MAN: I made a deal.
Beneficial to me.

07:41.156 --> 07:43.375
The other side is looking
to fill up their Strategy ranks.

07:43.506 --> 07:46.857
They're buying defectors
for a princely sum.

07:46.988 --> 07:48.990
Smuggling them across.

07:49.120 --> 07:52.123
-But I can't just leave.
-You haven't got a choice.

07:55.344 --> 07:57.520
Let's make something clear.

07:57.651 --> 08:01.132
You belong to this job,
Ian Shaw.

08:01.263 --> 08:03.961
If you ever feel the temptation
you felt with her,

08:04.092 --> 08:05.833
want to confide in someone,

08:05.963 --> 08:08.836
maybe want to run from it all,

08:08.966 --> 08:12.100
think about what
you see here today.

08:12.230 --> 08:13.928
This job will kill you

08:16.278 --> 08:18.541
and anyone you hold dear.

08:26.941 --> 08:30.379
[ exhales shakily ]

08:30.510 --> 08:32.337
[ phone vibrating ]

08:32.468 --> 08:35.384
[ sighs ]

08:42.652 --> 08:44.175
You okay?

08:44.306 --> 08:46.134
EMILY PRIME:
Yeah. Where are you?

08:46.264 --> 08:48.179
-On my way
to the address you gave me.
-Alone?

08:50.399 --> 08:52.662
-Of course.
-Call me when you're close.

08:52.793 --> 08:54.142
Look for me
outside the freight entrance

08:54.272 --> 08:56.492
around the back. Oh, I-Ian.

08:56.623 --> 08:58.494
I've got Howard with me.

09:02.803 --> 09:05.762
You're doing the right thing.

09:07.851 --> 09:09.244
Fuck you.

09:10.767 --> 09:12.552
[ woman seaking German over PA ]

09:14.858 --> 09:16.773
QUAYLE:
It was five years ago.

09:16.904 --> 09:18.993
WOMAN:
The time of your wedding.

09:19.123 --> 09:21.082
Yeah.

09:21.212 --> 09:24.346
Where did you conduct the affair
with Milla Castel?

09:24.476 --> 09:27.654
Various places. Hotel rooms.

09:27.784 --> 09:30.004
But it wasn't until yesterday

09:30.134 --> 09:32.310
you realized
your secretary was...

09:32.441 --> 09:35.792
It was Lambert,
told me that she was...

09:35.923 --> 09:38.316
the agent who's been siphoning
our intelligence

09:38.447 --> 09:40.580
-all these years.
-Shadow.

09:45.846 --> 09:49.501
So I asked Howard Silk...

09:49.632 --> 09:54.071
to get me a gun
so I could confront her.

09:54.202 --> 09:57.553
I only wish I'd gotten
to her sooner.

09:57.684 --> 10:00.948
Are you aware
of any other agents?

10:03.254 --> 10:05.953
-No, of course not.
-How are we supposed to...

10:06.083 --> 10:08.738
-God, he is so fucked.
-So much for the golden boy.

10:13.351 --> 10:18.052
[ praying in Arabic ]

10:35.765 --> 10:38.899
[ continues praying in Arabic ]

10:39.029 --> 10:40.814
[ knock on door ]

10:43.120 --> 10:45.775
-Oh, sorry. Um...
-It's okay.

10:45.906 --> 10:47.821
We searched
Milla Castel's place.

10:47.951 --> 10:49.649
She's definitely our mole.

10:49.779 --> 10:52.260
Hidden caches.
A couple of stolen documents.

10:52.390 --> 10:55.393
Looks like she's been
running Quayle for years.

10:55.524 --> 10:58.396
It lines up.

10:58.527 --> 11:00.442
Father-in-law's
gonna hit the ceiling

11:00.572 --> 11:02.313
when he finds out
Quayle is being held this way.

11:05.490 --> 11:07.754
Send him home. Guarded.

11:07.884 --> 11:10.321
We'll call it house arrest
until we figure something out.

11:10.452 --> 11:12.367
Okay.

11:24.814 --> 11:27.687
[ door unlocks ]

11:41.962 --> 11:44.007
♪

11:56.890 --> 11:58.761
Peter?

11:58.892 --> 12:00.720
What are you...

12:09.816 --> 12:12.514
It's not true, you know.

12:12.644 --> 12:15.604
That your life flashes
before your eyes.

12:15.735 --> 12:17.606
I just got one memory.

12:19.869 --> 12:23.699
It was the first time
Spencer smiled.

12:23.830 --> 12:26.397
We'd been trying to get her
to do it for ages.

12:26.528 --> 12:27.747
Do you remember?

12:29.009 --> 12:31.881
What-What's happened?

12:32.012 --> 12:33.753
Yeah, I'd just come back
from that trip.

12:35.972 --> 12:38.888
As soon as I picked her up,

12:39.019 --> 12:41.978
her whole face just lit up.

12:42.109 --> 12:44.894
Do you think
it was the same for her?

12:47.157 --> 12:50.160
Maybe she got one happy memory
before she died.

12:50.291 --> 12:51.988
Who are...

12:52.119 --> 12:54.774
Who are you talking about?

12:55.992 --> 12:58.952
Milla, my secretary.

12:59.082 --> 13:01.693
The one you had inside.

13:01.824 --> 13:04.435
The one you had
handling problems

13:04.566 --> 13:07.917
like Claude Lambert,
Edgar Brandt.

13:08.048 --> 13:10.441
She was... she was shaking.

13:10.572 --> 13:13.357
She didn't want to die. She...

13:15.142 --> 13:18.623
But she did it anyway.

13:18.754 --> 13:22.497
For your fucking cause.

13:22.627 --> 13:25.543
I didn't know that was the plan.

13:28.764 --> 13:30.940
But you knew there was a plan.

13:31.071 --> 13:33.638
And you knew about Milla.

13:35.510 --> 13:39.340
The very first morning
that she had there...

13:39.470 --> 13:42.386
she made me a cup of tea,

13:42.517 --> 13:44.345
exactly as I take it.

13:46.434 --> 13:48.392
I was so impressed.

13:50.742 --> 13:52.788
That was you...

13:52.919 --> 13:54.790
wasn't it?

13:54.921 --> 13:57.532
You told her.

13:57.662 --> 14:00.709
They wanted her to do
a good job.

14:00.840 --> 14:03.538
Yeah, well, she did.

14:03.668 --> 14:06.933
She was fucking perfect.

14:07.063 --> 14:08.848
Just like you.

14:10.110 --> 14:13.548
So why was she expendable?

14:13.678 --> 14:16.333
Why not let me take the fall?

14:17.769 --> 14:20.511
Because you're important, Peter.

14:24.254 --> 14:26.430
♪

14:44.753 --> 14:46.450
Do you pray, Howard?

14:47.669 --> 14:50.324
I'm not really religious.

14:50.454 --> 14:52.152
I do.

14:53.805 --> 14:55.938
Perform salatevery day.

14:56.069 --> 14:58.506
Not for answers--
I'm smart enough to know

14:58.636 --> 15:01.683
that if I ask for something,
it won't magically appear.

15:01.813 --> 15:03.728
No, I pray for clarity.

15:03.859 --> 15:07.558
That I'm on the right path,
and I should trust my instincts.

15:07.689 --> 15:10.213
Well, you know
I didn't kill anybody.

15:10.344 --> 15:13.086
I know. Mr. Quayle was just
asking you to get him a gun.

15:13.216 --> 15:15.305
It wasn't the murder weapon.

15:15.436 --> 15:18.352
Now, see, if he'd come to me,
you wouldn't have been involved,

15:18.482 --> 15:20.832
but for some reason he wanted
to handle this himself.

15:20.963 --> 15:22.791
Handle what?

15:22.922 --> 15:25.402
His secretary was
a sleeper agent.

15:25.533 --> 15:27.578
She was the one
who murdered four guards,

15:27.709 --> 15:29.580
as well as a source
we apprehended.

15:29.711 --> 15:32.670
He tried to confront her.
Now she's dead.

15:36.936 --> 15:39.242
They warned me,
after they read me in,

15:39.373 --> 15:40.896
that I would wonder...

15:41.027 --> 15:43.029
about their world, my other.

15:43.159 --> 15:45.031
That's what people do, isn't it?

15:45.161 --> 15:47.120
You just found out.

15:50.427 --> 15:52.473
I didn't wonder about my other.

15:52.603 --> 15:54.954
I thought about God.

15:55.084 --> 15:56.520
Two worlds.

15:56.651 --> 15:58.392
Two Meccas.

15:58.522 --> 16:01.525
If I pray toward mine,
they pray towards theirs.

16:01.656 --> 16:03.614
Who does God hear?

16:05.094 --> 16:07.923
And then this morning,
it hit me.

16:08.054 --> 16:09.751
God gave us both worlds.

16:09.881 --> 16:12.101
He's the creator of all things,
and if all things

16:12.232 --> 16:14.103
means two Meccas, then...

16:14.234 --> 16:16.323
God hears us both.

16:16.453 --> 16:19.108
There can be two truths.

16:22.285 --> 16:25.245
Why am I still being held?

16:25.375 --> 16:28.335
Because I see two truths
in you, Howard.

16:30.206 --> 16:32.252
One that says you're
just an innocent nobody

16:32.382 --> 16:34.863
dragged into this
because of his wife, his boss.

16:36.430 --> 16:39.128
But then I look at you...

16:39.259 --> 16:43.176
and I know in my heart
that there's a second truth.

16:43.306 --> 16:45.874
I just don't know what it is.

16:51.010 --> 16:53.664
[ sighs ]
Anyway, I called your wife.

16:53.795 --> 16:55.840
-You... you what?
-She's coming into the Office

16:55.971 --> 16:58.147
to confirm a few details
about the woman who's died.

16:58.278 --> 17:00.149
When she leaves,
you can go with her.

17:00.280 --> 17:02.499
You'll both be guarded
from here on out.

17:02.630 --> 17:04.327
Guarded? Why?

17:04.458 --> 17:06.199
Because she's very important.

17:08.244 --> 17:10.464
And because I feel like
I should trust you.

17:10.594 --> 17:12.553
But I don't.

17:15.947 --> 17:16.948
[ Temple knocks on door ]

17:17.079 --> 17:19.299
[ door opens ]

17:21.214 --> 17:22.824
[ bird cawing ]

17:24.695 --> 17:27.176
[ footsteps, rhythmic scraping ]

17:27.307 --> 17:30.049
[ footsteps,
rhythmic scraping continue ]

17:31.659 --> 17:33.748
[ Quayle Prime mumbling ]

17:40.407 --> 17:42.496
[ quietly ] No.
There's no stopping those two.

17:45.890 --> 17:47.675
Wait. Now, wait, here he comes.

17:49.372 --> 17:50.547
[ Quayle Prime
continues mumbling ]

17:50.678 --> 17:52.419
I knew Echo was
a classified prison.

17:52.549 --> 17:54.160
I had no idea it was like this.

17:55.335 --> 17:57.337
What did they do here?

17:57.467 --> 17:59.382
They, uh...

17:59.513 --> 18:01.558
extracted memories.

18:01.689 --> 18:03.647
-They...
-[ loud thump ]

18:03.778 --> 18:06.302
[ laughs softly ]

18:06.433 --> 18:08.304
I didn't think
I would see you again.

18:12.917 --> 18:14.441
SPORTSCASTER:
...this team.

18:14.571 --> 18:16.312
Watch out, here he comes...

18:16.443 --> 18:17.966
[ sportscaster continues
indistinctly ]

18:18.097 --> 18:20.229
I wasn't actually
looking for you.

18:20.360 --> 18:22.623
I was looking for Indigo.

18:22.753 --> 18:25.147
Their leader's
a woman called Mira.

18:27.149 --> 18:29.891
Top of Management's most wanted.

18:30.021 --> 18:31.762
Why would they do this?

18:31.893 --> 18:34.243
I don't know.

18:34.374 --> 18:37.507
And I don't know how
they found this place.

18:37.638 --> 18:40.119
No one knew
the location of Echo.

18:42.164 --> 18:44.035
[ scoffs softly ]

18:44.166 --> 18:45.167
Of course.

18:45.298 --> 18:46.516
What?

18:46.647 --> 18:48.605
Do you know that man?

18:57.614 --> 18:59.312
Osman Parash.

19:00.661 --> 19:03.838
Worked at the Office.

19:03.968 --> 19:06.797
And for Mira, evidently.

19:06.928 --> 19:09.626
He gave me these pills...

19:09.757 --> 19:11.759
before he sent me here.

19:11.889 --> 19:15.197
Said they were immunizations.

19:15.328 --> 19:16.981
I should have...

19:17.112 --> 19:19.810
What if that was
some kind of...

19:21.247 --> 19:23.423
What if I'mthe one who...

19:26.904 --> 19:28.863
[ scoffs softly ]

19:28.993 --> 19:31.692
I wonder if there's been
a moment in all of this

19:31.822 --> 19:34.129
when I wasn't being exploited.

19:34.260 --> 19:37.524
What about the man
they left with?

19:37.654 --> 19:38.873
Yanek.

19:39.003 --> 19:40.657
Uh...

19:40.788 --> 19:42.659
I-I can show you.

19:42.790 --> 19:44.226
SPORTSCASTER:
38-17.

19:44.357 --> 19:46.402
Saracens will be playing
Division One rugby again

19:46.533 --> 19:47.577
next year, and...

20:00.460 --> 20:02.679
[ sighs ]

20:02.810 --> 20:05.856
♪

20:31.012 --> 20:32.579
[ knocking ]

20:40.108 --> 20:42.023
[ loud knocking ]

20:43.938 --> 20:45.461
Is he home?

20:45.592 --> 20:47.507
He's sleeping.
What are you doing here?

20:47.637 --> 20:49.726
Dad?

20:49.857 --> 20:51.119
Get up.

20:51.250 --> 20:52.816
Roland.

20:52.947 --> 20:54.427
What-What's going on?

20:54.557 --> 20:56.255
They've called us in.

20:56.385 --> 20:58.735
Change your clothes.
I'll wait for you outside.

21:10.051 --> 21:11.444
You sure you're not hungry?

21:15.317 --> 21:17.188
Did you know?

21:18.277 --> 21:19.713
What?

21:19.843 --> 21:22.237
About his secretary.

21:22.368 --> 21:24.239
The running around.

21:24.370 --> 21:25.980
[ footsteps approaching ]

21:26.110 --> 21:27.721
Is everything all right?

21:32.595 --> 21:35.337
I heard about your confession.

21:36.556 --> 21:38.035
Lines up pretty nicely

21:38.166 --> 21:40.124
to that stupid car accident.

21:40.255 --> 21:42.257
Roland, that had nothing
to do with this.

21:42.388 --> 21:44.520
So I ask you again, Bunk.

21:44.651 --> 21:46.870
How long have you known
about his affair?

21:47.001 --> 21:49.743
Dad, stay out of this.

21:51.222 --> 21:54.225
You stupid fucking moron.

21:56.010 --> 21:58.317
Do you have any idea
how this makes her look,

21:58.447 --> 22:00.406
how it makes me look?

22:00.536 --> 22:02.538
We who brought you
into this family.

22:02.669 --> 22:05.324
-I'm so sorry.
-I endorsed your promotion.

22:05.454 --> 22:08.849
I brought you in on every
high-level Diplomacy meet,

22:08.979 --> 22:11.417
and Management,
all so you could prove your...

22:11.547 --> 22:13.984
[ chuckles ]

22:16.596 --> 22:18.554
[ Fancher chuckles quietly ]

22:18.685 --> 22:22.689
I did it because my daughter
was in love with you.

22:22.819 --> 22:26.170
Because I thought
she should be with a decent man.

22:26.301 --> 22:28.825
Not because you deserve it.
You don't deserve any of this.

22:28.956 --> 22:30.174
I know.
I've completely faltered.

22:30.305 --> 22:31.698
There's no excuse, I'm-I'm...

22:31.828 --> 22:34.004
-[ slams counter ]
-People are dead!

22:34.135 --> 22:35.963
-Because of you!
-Dad...

22:36.093 --> 22:37.573
I don't think
I should be hearing this.

22:37.704 --> 22:39.314
How could you let him
run around like this?

22:39.445 --> 22:40.271
Roland, it's not her fault.

22:40.402 --> 22:42.578
Shut up!

22:42.709 --> 22:45.755
[ clock ticking ]

22:48.976 --> 22:51.326
Why didn't you come to me?

22:51.457 --> 22:53.415
Brought Spencer.

22:55.112 --> 22:57.419
Leave him in the dust.

22:57.550 --> 23:00.030
I thought I raised you
to be stronger.

23:01.162 --> 23:03.207
Raised me?

23:03.338 --> 23:05.993
FANCHER:
Get in the car.

23:06.123 --> 23:08.169
What did you say?

23:08.299 --> 23:10.301
About raising me?

23:11.912 --> 23:13.130
-Clare.
-CLARE: No.

23:13.261 --> 23:14.610
Say it again.

23:14.741 --> 23:17.439
I thought I raised you
to be strong.

23:17.570 --> 23:19.441
To stand up
for what you believe in.

23:19.572 --> 23:21.574
To stand up
to little men like this.

23:21.704 --> 23:26.405
Not chase him around
and-and clean up after his mess.

23:26.535 --> 23:28.450
You don't know
the first thing about me.

23:30.060 --> 23:31.888
You see me
for who you want me to be.

23:32.019 --> 23:34.151
That's all you see.

23:34.282 --> 23:37.024
And when I fall short of some
false expectation, I'm to blame.

23:37.154 --> 23:38.721
I'm not that little girl

23:38.852 --> 23:40.810
you used to go skiing with
in Zermatt.

23:40.941 --> 23:43.552
The one who loved romance novels
and wore a lot of pink.

23:43.683 --> 23:45.989
I stand here in my own life,

23:46.120 --> 23:49.079
the one I built for myself,
so don't you dare walk in here

23:49.210 --> 23:51.038
and judge me
for the choices Imade,

23:51.168 --> 23:52.561
the man Ichose to marry.

23:55.912 --> 23:57.653
You have no power
over who I am.

24:03.833 --> 24:05.444
Get in the car.

24:11.928 --> 24:13.495
[ door opens ]

24:16.629 --> 24:18.761
[ indistinct chatter
over radio ]

24:23.070 --> 24:27.074
The other side sent
Ambassador Sy home this morning.

24:27.204 --> 24:29.816
Do-do you think they want
to reopen the doors?

24:35.082 --> 24:38.085
Do you even realize
how everything you do

24:38.215 --> 24:40.043
reflects right back on me?

24:41.392 --> 24:43.046
[ whispers ]
I do. Yeah.

24:43.177 --> 24:45.266
I recommended you for director.

24:45.396 --> 24:47.398
Yeah, I know,
and I will fix this.

24:47.529 --> 24:50.532
Good. You can start
by leaving her.

24:50.663 --> 24:51.620
What?

24:51.751 --> 24:52.752
Come on, Peter, please.

24:52.882 --> 24:54.144
She's too devoted.

24:55.581 --> 24:56.843
She doesn't know
what's best for her.

24:56.973 --> 24:59.323
If she did, she would've
left you a long time ago.

25:00.803 --> 25:03.632
She never used to be like this.

25:03.763 --> 25:05.939
Primary school,
other kids would make fun of her

25:06.069 --> 25:08.550
for the way she drew her S's.
She didn't care.

25:08.681 --> 25:10.813
She came home,
she laughed it off.

25:10.944 --> 25:13.468
She doesn't laugh anymore.

25:13.599 --> 25:15.688
Maybe it's the baby,
I don't know.

25:15.818 --> 25:17.777
She puts on this smile,

25:17.907 --> 25:20.997
but I can tell
she is not happy.

25:21.128 --> 25:24.000
You're never
gonna change, Peter,

25:24.131 --> 25:26.133
and neither is she.

25:26.263 --> 25:28.570
So I am begging you,
leave her.

25:31.007 --> 25:33.357
So she can be herself again.

25:33.488 --> 25:35.272
♪

25:38.145 --> 25:40.930
[ speaking German ]

25:51.114 --> 25:52.812
[ door locks ]

26:03.823 --> 26:05.868
Hi. I'm Nicole.
We spoke on the phone.

26:05.999 --> 26:08.001
-Nice to meet you.
-I work for Naya Temple.

26:08.131 --> 26:09.089
Thanks for coming.

26:09.219 --> 26:10.569
Please.

26:12.701 --> 26:15.922
We had a pretty long night.

26:18.707 --> 26:20.491
I think I remember this place.

26:20.622 --> 26:22.319
NICOLE:
That's what we are hoping.

26:24.974 --> 26:26.715
TEMPLE:
Tell me when you're ready.

26:29.718 --> 26:30.937
I'm ready.

26:50.521 --> 26:52.523
TEMPLE:
Is this Shadow?

26:52.654 --> 26:54.525
I don't know.

27:00.140 --> 27:02.533
It could be... maybe.

27:02.664 --> 27:05.972
She-she had dark hair like her.

27:06.102 --> 27:08.714
So, maybe, y-yes.

27:08.844 --> 27:10.759
Oh, I...

27:15.546 --> 27:18.071
Can you tell me anything
else about her?

27:18.201 --> 27:21.596
She was a secretary in Strategy.
Milla Castel.

27:21.727 --> 27:23.424
She worked for one
of our deputy directors,

27:23.554 --> 27:25.948
-Peter Quayle.
-Quayle.

27:26.079 --> 27:27.994
I never worked under him.

27:28.124 --> 27:30.257
A different division.

27:33.390 --> 27:35.871
But that makes sense, somehow.

27:36.002 --> 27:36.959
How?

27:38.744 --> 27:40.006
Whoever Shadow was,

27:40.136 --> 27:42.791
she was definitely close
to Quayle.

27:42.922 --> 27:44.967
There were documents

27:45.098 --> 27:47.883
that came directly
from his department,

27:48.014 --> 27:49.406
his desk, even.

27:53.193 --> 27:55.151
I'm sorry.
I can't remember anything else.

27:55.282 --> 27:57.153
This was very helpful.

27:57.284 --> 27:59.242
We have to be careful now.

27:59.373 --> 28:01.244
The source you gave me,
Claude Lambert,

28:01.375 --> 28:03.159
was killed by this woman,
in our custody.

28:03.290 --> 28:05.684
Indigo's likely going
to react to her death.

28:07.598 --> 28:10.340
I'm gonna have you guarded
from this point forward.

28:10.471 --> 28:13.474
You think
that more is gonna happen?

28:13.604 --> 28:15.563
I do.

28:17.783 --> 28:19.349
[ phone vibrating ]

28:19.480 --> 28:21.308
[ footsteps approaching ]

28:24.267 --> 28:25.573
[ phone beeps ]

28:25.704 --> 28:27.749
Hello?

28:27.880 --> 28:29.708
SPENCER:
I need to see you.

28:31.144 --> 28:33.146
Okay. When?

28:33.276 --> 28:35.191
SPENCER: I'll pick you up
at Lichterfelde West station

28:35.322 --> 28:37.367
in an hour.

28:37.498 --> 28:40.327
[ woman speaking German
over P.A. ]

28:49.075 --> 28:50.816
I'm glad you came.

28:50.946 --> 28:53.470
I'm glad you called.

28:53.601 --> 28:55.516
You okay?

28:55.646 --> 28:57.518
Yeah, just a rough morning.

28:57.648 --> 28:59.128
[ children giggling ]

28:59.259 --> 29:01.740
-Where are we going?
-To meet some friends.

29:15.666 --> 29:18.452
[ car door closes ]

29:18.582 --> 29:20.497
WOMAN:
She shouldn't be here.

29:20.628 --> 29:23.283
We need all the help
we can get right now.

29:23.413 --> 29:25.589
Doesn't she have
other work to do?

29:25.720 --> 29:28.201
Imade the call.

29:28.331 --> 29:30.203
WOMAN:
Whatever.

29:31.857 --> 29:33.815
-What was that?
-Don't worry about it.

29:33.946 --> 29:36.470
Clare?

29:36.600 --> 29:38.689
Amelia.

29:40.430 --> 29:42.345
Mikael.

29:44.260 --> 29:46.088
Carrie.

29:49.004 --> 29:51.615
This is your cell?

29:51.746 --> 29:54.053
You've all been together
all this time?

29:54.183 --> 29:56.969
Our placements didn't require
isolation the way yours did.

29:57.099 --> 29:59.058
We were lucky.

29:59.188 --> 30:01.190
AMELIA:
Don't listen to him.

30:01.321 --> 30:03.366
We got each other,
you got the glory.

30:03.497 --> 30:04.846
[ scoffs ]

30:04.977 --> 30:07.153
I've missed you so much.

30:07.283 --> 30:09.285
Yeah.

30:09.416 --> 30:11.461
I've missed you all, too.

30:11.592 --> 30:13.420
[ footsteps approaching ]

30:16.249 --> 30:18.077
Hello, Clare.

30:18.207 --> 30:20.166
Ethel.

30:22.081 --> 30:24.126
It's an honor to see you.

30:24.257 --> 30:25.911
SPENCER:
Let's work fast.

30:26.041 --> 30:27.826
We don't have a lot of time.

30:29.871 --> 30:32.004
This slip was registered
in Milla's name.

30:32.134 --> 30:33.570
We have to clear everything out

30:33.701 --> 30:34.920
before they start digging
through her records.

30:35.050 --> 30:36.443
What is this?

30:36.573 --> 30:39.620
SPENCER:
Our last steps.

30:39.750 --> 30:42.275
By now, Mira should have
Management gathering together,

30:42.405 --> 30:44.407
so we've got to be ready.

30:44.538 --> 30:46.453
Ready for what?

30:48.629 --> 30:50.718
Can you grab the other end?

31:00.119 --> 31:02.817
Yanek ran this place,

31:02.948 --> 31:07.082
but he was also a prisoner.

31:07.213 --> 31:09.171
He and this group
of scientists were here

31:09.302 --> 31:10.912
when the Crossing began.

31:11.043 --> 31:13.219
They were the first
to experiment with it.

31:19.790 --> 31:21.967
This... this girl.

31:24.752 --> 31:26.623
I know this face.

31:26.754 --> 31:28.669
This is Mira.

31:28.799 --> 31:30.236
Look at the resemblance.

31:31.498 --> 31:32.760
She's his daughter.

31:32.891 --> 31:36.416
But the effort of finding Echo
to-to break him out.

31:36.546 --> 31:39.419
That's not just a little girl
looking for her daddy.

31:39.549 --> 31:42.422
Why? Why was this man
a prisoner here?

31:42.552 --> 31:44.467
HOWARD:
He only said it was

31:44.598 --> 31:47.427
penance for a crime
committed long ago.

31:49.516 --> 31:52.301
You said these scientists knew

31:52.432 --> 31:53.955
about the Crossing
from the beginning?

31:54.086 --> 31:55.609
Yes.

32:02.050 --> 32:04.139
Maybe...

32:04.270 --> 32:06.098
Maybe this is Management.

32:06.228 --> 32:09.231
The same people in both worlds.

32:09.362 --> 32:12.147
It'd certainly explain why they
have to hide their faces,

32:12.278 --> 32:14.280
and Mira's father
is one of them.

32:14.410 --> 32:18.371
So you think it's possible that
all these men killed here today,

32:18.501 --> 32:22.027
the children at that school,
the attack on my wife,

32:22.157 --> 32:26.683
all stems from some... family
squabble on the Fourth Floor?

32:26.814 --> 32:29.251
[ sighs ] I don't know.
I'm out of my depth.

32:29.382 --> 32:32.646
That's the way I've felt
since this whole thing began.

32:32.776 --> 32:34.648
[ phone ringing ]

32:38.695 --> 32:39.653
Yep.

32:42.351 --> 32:43.439
Okay.

32:43.570 --> 32:45.398
Yeah, I'll meet you there.

32:47.052 --> 32:50.272
Howard, that was Ian.

32:50.403 --> 32:53.884
He's close.

32:54.015 --> 32:54.973
I'm...

32:55.103 --> 32:58.237
I'm sorry, it had to be him.

32:58.367 --> 33:00.282
He's the only one I can trust.

33:03.329 --> 33:05.157
[ groans softly ]

33:06.419 --> 33:08.421
Emily...

33:08.551 --> 33:11.380
I won't be a prisoner anymore.

33:11.511 --> 33:14.905
I'm not going back
into anyone's custody.

33:15.036 --> 33:17.386
Not after all this.

33:17.517 --> 33:20.737
Okay.

33:20.868 --> 33:21.956
I understand.

33:24.089 --> 33:26.004
I'll tell him.

33:28.049 --> 33:29.964
[ woman speaking German
over P.A. ]

33:42.020 --> 33:44.065
[ sighs ]

33:44.196 --> 33:46.198
[ indistinct chatter ]

33:48.330 --> 33:50.332
Mr. Quayle.

33:53.814 --> 33:56.077
-Ah, Mr. Silk.
-They let you out, I see.

33:56.208 --> 33:58.297
Yeah. Thank you so much
for your help yesterday.

33:58.427 --> 33:59.907
Excuse me.
I have a meeting.

34:00.038 --> 34:02.388
Hey, hey, hey,
we're not out of this.

34:02.518 --> 34:03.954
Okay.

34:04.085 --> 34:06.740
She has us.
I got to talk to your wife.

34:06.870 --> 34:09.264
S-Sorry.
You need something from me?

34:09.395 --> 34:12.833
Like it or not,
we are in this together, okay?

34:12.963 --> 34:15.314
I got to find out
what Clare's group is gonna do,

34:15.444 --> 34:17.577
or Temple will bring us
both down.

34:17.707 --> 34:20.014
Get some rest, Howard.

34:20.145 --> 34:23.235
You must be exhausted,
a man of your age.

34:26.325 --> 34:27.413
[ door buzzes ]

34:32.113 --> 34:34.202
[ woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A. ]

34:34.333 --> 34:36.161
[ door buzzes, opens ]

34:38.424 --> 34:39.381
[ door closes ]

34:41.905 --> 34:43.342
I worried about you all night.

34:43.472 --> 34:45.474
Are you okay?

34:45.605 --> 34:48.521
These men will drive you home,
stay with you at all hours.

34:48.651 --> 34:50.436
You'll be safe in their care.

34:52.307 --> 34:54.135
[ engine starts ]

35:12.240 --> 35:14.024
[ stove burner clicking ]

35:14.155 --> 35:17.289
EMILY SILK:
You must be exhausted.

35:28.909 --> 35:30.171
PRIME:
So much coffee.

35:30.302 --> 35:31.999
How long do you think

35:32.130 --> 35:33.914
before they come knocking
for the bathroom?

35:35.785 --> 35:39.049
They're supposed
to be helping us.

35:39.180 --> 35:43.053
I brought you into all this.
I'm so sorry.

35:43.184 --> 35:44.838
It's not your fault.

35:44.968 --> 35:48.058
[ sighs ]

35:48.189 --> 35:50.757
Look at what our lives
have become.

35:56.850 --> 35:59.113
Did you tell Naya Temple

35:59.244 --> 36:01.768
about that, uh, source
that you met the other day?

36:01.898 --> 36:03.639
[ sighs ]
Howard.

36:06.512 --> 36:08.905
Emily, I-I wish
you would let me in.

36:09.036 --> 36:10.516
Maybe I could help you remember.

36:10.646 --> 36:11.647
Okay.

36:11.778 --> 36:13.475
Sure.

36:13.606 --> 36:15.390
I'll show you
what happens when I do.

36:20.439 --> 36:24.486
These are the people
who were killed last month.

36:24.617 --> 36:26.401
18 names.

36:26.532 --> 36:29.099
Every single one of them,
a member of my team.

36:29.230 --> 36:32.364
I've been staring
at these faces all week.

36:32.494 --> 36:35.889
Friends, trusted allies,

36:36.019 --> 36:37.978
every single one of them killed.

36:40.328 --> 36:42.548
You really are
the only one I have left.

36:46.900 --> 36:48.684
I need to start
piecing this together.

36:50.425 --> 36:53.646
I need something
to jog my memory.

36:53.776 --> 36:56.344
Before something awful
happens again.

37:04.613 --> 37:06.093
SPENCER:
Thank you for helping.

37:06.224 --> 37:08.095
You didn't need my help.

37:10.228 --> 37:12.012
Why did you bring me
here today?

37:14.014 --> 37:17.191
I just thought you might want
to see the others.

37:17.322 --> 37:21.369
After yesterday,
the way you were speaking...

37:21.500 --> 37:24.807
I know the years have been hard,
but you're not alone.

37:26.200 --> 37:27.767
We've both been alone.

37:27.897 --> 37:29.725
No, see, we're not, Clare.

37:29.856 --> 37:32.424
Our friends-- they're around us
even when we can't see them.

37:32.554 --> 37:36.166
That's what Mira
has built for us.

37:36.297 --> 37:38.560
And I wanted you
to remember that.

37:45.959 --> 37:47.874
Did you know
what happened to my parents?

37:48.004 --> 37:50.790
[ passing car horn honking ]

37:52.357 --> 37:55.055
I found something recently.

37:55.185 --> 37:57.405
A recording from Lambert.

37:59.277 --> 38:01.453
It was Pope's voice
from years ago.

38:01.583 --> 38:05.195
He told Lambert that my parents
didn't die from the flu.

38:05.326 --> 38:07.981
They were killed.

38:08.111 --> 38:10.592
By Mira.

38:10.723 --> 38:12.202
[ scoffs ]
It's a lie.

38:12.333 --> 38:13.726
I heard his voice.

38:13.856 --> 38:15.641
She would never be capable
of something like that.

38:15.771 --> 38:16.990
After everything she has done?

38:17.120 --> 38:18.948
Come on, Spencer.

38:19.079 --> 38:22.387
She had my parents murdered
so that I would hate this world.

38:22.517 --> 38:24.998
Fine. So what?

38:25.128 --> 38:26.913
Others' parents did die.

38:27.043 --> 38:30.046
They killed millions, Clare.

38:30.177 --> 38:32.788
You can't make a child
understand millions.

38:32.919 --> 38:34.834
It has to be personal.

38:34.964 --> 38:36.531
Easy to say
when you're not the child.

38:38.707 --> 38:40.709
My parents gave me away to her,

38:40.840 --> 38:42.842
like sending me off
to summer camp.

38:44.583 --> 38:46.324
We've all made sacrifices.

38:46.454 --> 38:48.935
I killed my other
with my bare hands,

38:49.065 --> 38:50.676
used her life like a game piece.

38:52.808 --> 38:56.029
And these others--
they just look at me

38:56.159 --> 38:58.292
like I'm some kind of hero
for that.

38:58.423 --> 39:00.729
What if we're not really
the heroes?

39:04.994 --> 39:06.344
[ tires squealing ]

39:08.302 --> 39:10.304
You killed a nobody housewife

39:10.435 --> 39:13.263
who would never amount
to anything in any world.

39:13.394 --> 39:15.701
You took her wasted life
and gave it meaning.

39:15.831 --> 39:17.920
I don't think
you really believe that.

39:18.051 --> 39:19.487
This world

39:19.618 --> 39:23.796
has done so many cruel,
horrible things.

39:23.926 --> 39:27.495
We were chosen to right them.

39:27.626 --> 39:30.237
And I'm thankful for that
every day.

39:30.368 --> 39:32.152
You should be, too.

39:37.853 --> 39:39.899
You're right.

39:40.987 --> 39:42.597
I'm sorry.

39:50.823 --> 39:52.041
[ engine turns off ]

39:52.172 --> 39:54.435
[ indistinct chatter ]

39:56.742 --> 39:58.265
SPENCER:
Clare.

40:07.100 --> 40:09.189
This will be done soon.

40:09.319 --> 40:11.104
We'll be free forever.

40:11.234 --> 40:13.759
We'll get to be us.

40:13.889 --> 40:16.109
And then what?

40:23.769 --> 40:26.075
[ woman speaking German
over P.A. ]

40:31.211 --> 40:33.474
QUAYLE:
Hi, Clare.

40:33.605 --> 40:36.129
Could you tell Spencer
that I love her?

40:36.259 --> 40:39.654
LEON:
Stick to the script, please.

40:39.785 --> 40:41.787
QUAYLE:
The main server crashed,

40:41.917 --> 40:44.180
and we have to stay
at the office

40:44.311 --> 40:47.140
till the computers
come back online,

40:47.270 --> 40:50.448
so security can log us out.

40:53.146 --> 40:55.714
Clare, I love you.

41:15.081 --> 41:16.865
After you.

41:20.913 --> 41:22.392
Let's get underway.

41:25.265 --> 41:26.396
-[ door closes ]
-[ sighs ]

41:26.527 --> 41:29.269
No one else knows
about this meeting.

41:29.399 --> 41:31.227
It isn't on the books.

41:31.358 --> 41:32.620
It never happened.

41:32.751 --> 41:35.667
As you probably know,

41:35.797 --> 41:39.322
Mr. Sy has been returned to
our world from the other side.

41:39.453 --> 41:42.325
He brought with him a message.

41:42.456 --> 41:45.328
Their Management would like to
meet with ours face-to-face.

41:45.459 --> 41:48.723
In undisclosed
other side territory.

41:48.854 --> 41:50.856
This meeting tomorrow
will be the first

41:50.986 --> 41:52.684
in person in decades.

41:52.814 --> 41:53.946
TEMPLE:
Sorry, I just have

41:54.076 --> 41:55.600
to raise a procedural concern.

41:55.730 --> 41:57.079
Why is Peter Quayle
in this meeting?

41:59.038 --> 42:02.302
He's deputy director
of Strategy.

42:02.432 --> 42:03.956
Yes, and I'd say

42:04.086 --> 42:05.958
his judgment these days
has been rather suspect.

42:06.088 --> 42:08.003
Wouldn't you?

42:08.134 --> 42:11.964
Peter Quayle let a spy endanger
his office and this institution.

42:12.094 --> 42:13.922
How can we be sure that,
by keeping him involved,

42:14.053 --> 42:15.707
that Management won't be
walking straight into the trap

42:15.837 --> 42:17.360
-of these terrorists?
-FANCHER: Well, you will find

42:17.491 --> 42:19.493
no defense from me

42:19.624 --> 42:22.322
when it comes to the personal
antics of Peter Quayle.

42:22.452 --> 42:23.845
Wonderful. Let's escort him out.

42:23.976 --> 42:25.455
I would like to remind you,
however,

42:25.586 --> 42:27.980
that Milla Castel was exposed

42:28.110 --> 42:29.677
and killed by Peter.

42:29.808 --> 42:31.636
After a five-year affair.

42:31.766 --> 42:34.552
Okay, this is an inappropriate
forum to have this conversation.

42:34.682 --> 42:36.075
You mean because it involves
your son-in-law?

42:37.772 --> 42:40.340
Okay. Well...
[ chuckles ]

42:40.470 --> 42:43.082
now we're getting personal.

42:43.212 --> 42:45.911
[ exhales ] Peter's job title
has nothing to do

42:46.041 --> 42:47.652
with the fact that he's married
to my daughter.

42:47.782 --> 42:50.306
Look, I know
this office has thrived

42:50.437 --> 42:52.352
on a certain inside way
of dealing with things.

42:52.482 --> 42:54.223
-Excuse me?
-I'm guessing
you call it loyalty.

42:54.354 --> 42:56.225
Excuse me?

42:56.356 --> 42:58.053
Loyalty. Yes.

42:58.184 --> 43:01.666
Loyalty is the pillar
of our work here.

43:01.796 --> 43:04.756
There are foxes in the henhouse.

43:04.886 --> 43:08.020
We must defend the integrity
of this institution!

43:08.150 --> 43:09.891
No, Mr. Fancher.

43:10.022 --> 43:12.024
I've been watching this
long enough to know what I see.

43:12.154 --> 43:13.634
It's not the institution
you defend around here;

43:13.765 --> 43:15.331
it's the people hiding
behind it.

43:15.462 --> 43:17.072
People who look like you,
act like you,

43:17.203 --> 43:19.074
and prey on the blindness
of the entire system.

43:19.205 --> 43:21.599
Well, I don't look like you.
So let me give you the facts.

43:21.729 --> 43:23.426
There aren't just foxes
in your henhouse.

43:23.557 --> 43:26.647
You are living in a henhouse
built by foxes.

43:26.778 --> 43:28.649
And if you people don't wake up,
then pretty soon,

43:28.780 --> 43:30.259
-there's gonna be no hens left.
-FANCHER: You're out of line.

43:30.390 --> 43:32.087
We're gonna sidebar
this discussion.

43:32.218 --> 43:34.960
No, Roland.

43:35.090 --> 43:36.570
She's right.

43:39.094 --> 43:42.054
We are. We're completely blind
to the people close to us.

43:43.185 --> 43:46.841
We really are.

43:46.972 --> 43:50.802
I couldn't see someone
right next to me

43:50.932 --> 43:53.369
for who she really was.

43:53.500 --> 43:57.373
And that put everyone here
in danger.

43:57.504 --> 43:59.027
And when I found out the truth,

43:59.158 --> 44:00.768
when I found out
the truth about her,

44:00.899 --> 44:03.858
I didn't do the right thing
and bring her in.

44:05.077 --> 44:07.035
I tried to protect myself.

44:07.166 --> 44:10.952
My job, my status.

44:11.083 --> 44:13.433
Things that I wanted.

44:15.609 --> 44:18.438
Which is why
I can't work here anymore.

44:18.568 --> 44:21.267
FANCHER: Peter,
what are you talking about?

44:21.397 --> 44:24.052
It's the only way to ensure
everyone else stays safe.

44:24.183 --> 44:26.359
I'm the liability.

44:26.489 --> 44:29.188
I'm sorry.

44:29.318 --> 44:30.363
I resign.

44:32.452 --> 44:34.454
♪

44:48.120 --> 44:49.121
This is Ian.

44:50.296 --> 44:51.689
There's another car.

44:54.735 --> 44:56.606
Goddamn it, Ian.

45:05.833 --> 45:07.705
What the hell's going on?

45:07.835 --> 45:09.141
YORKE:
Hello, Emily.

45:09.271 --> 45:11.012
EMILY PRIME:
What's he doing here?

45:11.143 --> 45:14.363
Thought our arrangement
was pretty clear.

45:14.494 --> 45:17.671
You haven't been in touch
in a while.

45:17.802 --> 45:19.412
-Mira was right here.
-[ car doors open, close ]

45:19.542 --> 45:20.935
With all of her people.

45:23.329 --> 45:26.680
Who are these guys?

45:26.811 --> 45:29.509
And why are they standing ready,
like I'm some kind of...

45:29.639 --> 45:31.729
SHAW:
Everyone stand down.

45:31.859 --> 45:33.948
We're on the same side here.

45:34.079 --> 45:35.515
EMILY PRIME:
Doesn't feel like that, Ian.

45:35.645 --> 45:36.951
Not from where I'm standing.

45:37.082 --> 45:39.475
You've done some great work,
Emily.

45:39.606 --> 45:42.391
Upstairs just wants to know
what you've learned.

45:42.522 --> 45:44.567
Maybe they're afraid
I've learned too much.

45:44.698 --> 45:47.092
Maybe they're trying
to put a lid on it.

45:47.222 --> 45:49.007
I assure you,
that's not the case.

45:49.137 --> 45:51.487
Put your gun away.

45:51.618 --> 45:53.272
And come in.

45:53.402 --> 45:55.883
I came out here
to do the goddamn mission

45:56.014 --> 45:57.711
you sent me to
in the first place.

45:57.842 --> 45:59.539
And we'll help with that.

45:59.669 --> 46:01.497
You can bring Howard Silk.

46:01.628 --> 46:02.629
HOWARD:
No.

46:02.760 --> 46:05.458
I'm not going back.

46:05.588 --> 46:07.112
YORKE:
Keep your gun on her.

46:07.242 --> 46:10.289
I'm done being
everybody's prisoner.

46:10.419 --> 46:12.944
Stop, Howard.
It's not about you.

46:13.074 --> 46:14.380
You're right.
It's not about me.

46:14.510 --> 46:16.948
It never has been.

46:17.078 --> 46:18.688
I shouldn't even be here.

46:18.819 --> 46:20.734
Then step aside.

46:20.865 --> 46:23.389
No.

46:23.519 --> 46:25.913
You need to let us go.

46:26.044 --> 46:28.698
[ chuckles softly ]
Or we just take you out,

46:28.829 --> 46:30.831
because no one gives a shit
about you, Howard.

46:32.137 --> 46:33.268
EMILY PRIME:
Ian.

46:36.706 --> 46:39.579
No one is shooting anyone.

46:41.886 --> 46:45.150
YORKE:
Otto, put 'em down.

47:00.339 --> 47:02.254
[ groaning ]

47:07.520 --> 47:09.130
[ grunting ]

47:12.655 --> 47:13.918
[ gasps ]

47:15.876 --> 47:18.226
[ grunting ]

47:19.445 --> 47:20.968
[ panting, groaning ]

47:23.579 --> 47:25.059
-[ shouts ]
-[ groans ]

47:28.323 --> 47:29.847
[ gunshot ]

47:29.977 --> 47:31.936
[ engine starts ]

47:32.066 --> 47:34.199
[ panting ]

47:37.942 --> 47:39.508
That was so stupid.

47:39.639 --> 47:41.423
What were you thinking?

47:41.554 --> 47:44.513
[ groans softly ]

47:44.644 --> 47:47.429
Howard, Jesus.

47:47.560 --> 47:49.954
[ exhales ]

47:50.084 --> 47:52.347
[ birds chirping ]

47:54.088 --> 47:56.308
[ door opens ]

47:58.832 --> 48:01.052
I'm gonna go run a few errands.

48:01.182 --> 48:02.967
Groceries. This and that.

48:03.097 --> 48:04.882
On foot.

48:05.012 --> 48:08.711
Unless, uh, one of you guys
wants to give me a ride.

48:10.278 --> 48:12.585
Worth a try.

48:19.244 --> 48:21.420
[ woman speaking German
over P.A. ]

48:25.163 --> 48:27.513
♪

48:52.277 --> 48:54.888
[ woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A. ]

48:56.542 --> 48:58.936
♪

49:00.807 --> 49:03.027
[ siren wailing in distance ]

49:08.032 --> 49:10.251
[ soft music playing ]

49:12.340 --> 49:14.038
Where's Spencer?

49:14.168 --> 49:15.387
I just put her down.

49:15.517 --> 49:16.823
Good. We have to go.

49:16.954 --> 49:19.434
Go?

49:19.565 --> 49:21.523
I'm alive because I'm important
to them, right?

49:21.654 --> 49:23.351
If I'm useless, then I'm dead.

49:23.482 --> 49:25.092
What the hell
are you talking about?

49:25.223 --> 49:26.398
I quit my job today.

49:26.528 --> 49:29.444
What the fuck?

49:29.575 --> 49:32.230
I'm tired of getting yanked
around on strings, Clare.

49:32.360 --> 49:34.449
And, you know what,
I think you are, too.

49:34.580 --> 49:36.799
What you've done is put
enormous targets on our backs.

49:36.930 --> 49:39.106
Yeah. Also, Howard Silk's
on his way, so we run.

49:39.237 --> 49:40.629
It's not that simple.

49:40.760 --> 49:42.457
Pack a bag.
We get out of here.

49:42.588 --> 49:45.112
There are guards outside.

49:45.243 --> 49:46.940
-Fentanyl,
like we used on Lambert.
-[ scoffs ]

49:48.898 --> 49:50.030
CLARE:
There's nowhere to go.

49:50.161 --> 49:52.685
Hotels, safe houses.
They-They'd find us.

49:52.815 --> 49:55.079
I don't know, Clare!
But we run or we are dead.

49:55.209 --> 49:56.689
And, listen,
I never gave you an ultimatum.

49:56.819 --> 49:58.212
I never said,
"Your cause or me,"

49:58.343 --> 50:00.084
because I knew
what you would choose.

50:00.214 --> 50:02.216
But I'm leaving tonight,
with Spencer,

50:02.347 --> 50:04.914
and I want my family
to stay together.

50:05.045 --> 50:07.221
So you tell me,
what's it gonna be?

50:07.352 --> 50:09.310
♪

50:33.813 --> 50:37.686
♪ There's something here
I've got to have ♪

50:37.817 --> 50:41.647
♪

50:41.777 --> 50:45.738
♪ I've got to see
if this could be ♪

50:45.868 --> 50:49.872
♪ The first wave of
love ♪

50:50.003 --> 50:51.657
♪

50:51.787 --> 50:54.268
♪ Taste my lips

50:55.400 --> 50:57.880
♪ Touch my skin

51:00.492 --> 51:05.149
♪ Tell ourselves,
dive in ♪

51:07.760 --> 51:09.675
♪ Come see

51:11.111 --> 51:14.549
♪ Come swim with me

51:14.680 --> 51:16.682
♪

51:22.601 --> 51:24.081
[ engine turns off ]

51:30.609 --> 51:33.786
We'll be safe here.

51:33.916 --> 51:36.049
What is this place?

51:36.180 --> 51:38.269
It's where I grew up.

51:38.399 --> 51:41.489
On the other side, at least.

51:42.664 --> 51:44.623
It was my home.

51:44.753 --> 51:47.104
Indigo.
